4. NUTRIENT CLOSED-LOOP & WASTE PROCESSING

4.1 Supercritical Water Oxidation (SCWO): The Metabolic Bridge

Process Parameters:

· Temperature: 374–650°C (optimized for organic destruction)
· Pressure: 22.1–30 MPa (above critical point of water)
· Residence time: 60–180 seconds
· Oxidant: Pure O₂ (from agricultural surplus)
· Catalyst: None required (autogenous reaction)

Input Streams (Daily per 100 persons):

· Human solid waste: 25 kg
· Inedible plant biomass: 50 kg
· Food processing waste: 15 kg
· Microbial bioreactor excess: 10 kg
· Total: ~100 kg organic input

Output Products:

1. Sterile water: 85–90 kg (meets potable standards)
2. CO₂: 25–30 kg (direct to agricultural atmosphere)
3. Mineral ash: 5–8 kg (P, K, Ca, Mg, micronutrients)
4. Heat: 15–25 kW thermal energy

Technical Specifications:

· Reactor material: Titanium-6Al-4V alloy with zirconia ceramic lining
· Pressure vessel: 316L stainless steel with autofrettage hardening
· Maintenance: Robotic ash clearance every 24 hours
· Redundancy: Dual reactors at 60% capacity each
· Safety: Triple pressure relief + explosive decompression containment

4.2 Nitrogen Management System

Sources & Recovery:

```
Source           Quantity (g/person/day)  Recovery Method     Efficiency
------           -----------------------  ---------------     ----------
Urine            10–12 N                  Vacuum distillation  85%
Feces            1–2 N                    SCWO                 70%
Plant residue    3–5 N                    SCWO                 80%
Atmospheric      0.5–1 N                  Biological fixation  90%
```

Total Recovery: 12–15 g N/person/day (meets 100% agricultural demand)

Fertilizer Production:

· NPK formulations: Custom blends per crop requirements
· Delivery: Automated dosing to hydroponic and regolith systems
· Monitoring: Real-time ion-selective electrode measurements
· Buffer capacity: 45-day supply in pressurized tanks

4.3 Mineral Recovery & Balancing

Critical Elements Recovery Rates:

· Phosphorus (P): 90–95% (limiting nutrient on Mars)
· Potassium (K): 85–90%
· Calcium (Ca): 80–85%
· Magnesium (Mg): 75–80%
· Micronutrients (Fe, Zn, Cu, Mn): 60–70%

Supplementation Strategy:

· Phase 1 (Years 0–2): 30% imported minerals
· Phase 2 (Years 2–5): 10% imported minerals
· Phase 3 (Years 5+): 100% closed-loop (supplemented by Martian regolith processing)

