5. AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTION PHASING

5.1 Phase 1: Survival & Establishment (Sol 0–500)

Primary Goal: Rapid calorie production and system validation
Systems: 90% hydroponics/aeroponics, 10% treated regolith trials
Crop Selection:

· Leafy greens: Lettuce, spinach, kale (20–30 day cycles)
· Microgreens: Broccoli, radish, sunflower (10–14 day cycles)
· Algae: Spirulina, chlorella (continuous harvest)
· Root crops: Radish, carrot (fast varieties)

Production Targets:

· Calories: 1,500 kcal/person/day (50% of requirement)
· Protein: 40 g/person/day (from algae + leafy greens)
· System closure: 70% water, 60% nutrients recycled

Key Activities:

· Starter Culture establishment and multiplication
· Pollinator colony foundation (incubation)
· SCWO system commissioning and optimization

5.2 Phase 2: Expansion & Diversification (Sol 500–1800)

Primary Goal: Calorie sufficiency and dietary diversity
Systems: 50% hydroponics, 50% treated regolith
Crop Expansion:

· Staples: Potato, sweet potato (high calorie yield)
· Grains: Dwarf wheat, quinoa (space-efficient)
· Legumes: Soybeans, lentils (protein + nitrogen fixation)
· Fruiting: Tomatoes, peppers, strawberries (pollinator-dependent)

Production Targets:

· Calories: 2,800 kcal/person/day (93% of requirement)
· Protein: 70 g/person/day (complete amino acid profile)
· Vitamins: 100% of RDAs from fresh produce
· System closure: 90% water, 85% nutrients recycled

Key Activities:

· Pollinator colonies fully operational
· Soil microbiome maturity monitoring
· Inter-cropping and polyculture optimization

5.3 Phase 3: Autonomy & Resilience (Sol 1800+)

Primary Goal: Complete food sovereignty with surplus buffer
Systems: 30% hydroponics, 70% treated regolith polyculture
Crop Maturity:

· Perennials: Fruit trees (dwarf varieties), berry bushes
· Diversity: 50+ crop species in rotation
· Specialty: Herbs, spices, medicinal plants
· Fiber: Hemp, flax for materials

Production Targets:

· Calories: 3,200 kcal/person/day (107% of requirement)
· Protein: 90 g/person/day (excess for processing)
· Surplus: 20% buffer for storage/emergencies
· System closure: 95% water, 95% nutrients recycled

Key Activities:

· Seed saving and cultivar adaptation to Mars conditions
· Ecosystem services optimization (pollination, pest control)
· Genetic diversity maintenance

