6. TREATED REGOLITH CULTIVATION PROTOCOL

6.1 Six-Stage Detoxification Process

Stage 1: Mechanical Preparation

· Rock removal (>2 cm): Vibratory sieving
· Particle sizing: 0.05–2 mm optimal range
· Magnetic separation: Remove metallic particles

Stage 2: Perchlorate Removal

· Method: Aqueous leaching with temperature cycling
· Solvent: Martian water (pre-deuterium reduction)
· Efficiency: 99.9% ClO₄⁻ removal
· Byproduct: Chloride salts (processed for Cl₂ production)

Stage 3: Electrochemical Refinement

· Process: Electrodialysis of leachate
· Recovery: Salts for industrial use
· Water: 95% recycled to leaching stage

Stage 4: pH & Nutrient Balancing

· Acid neutralization: Calcium carbonate addition
· Target pH: 6.5–7.2 (crop-specific optimization)
· Cation exchange: Zeolite addition for nutrient retention

Stage 5: Thermal Volatilization

· Temperature: 350°C for 2 hours
· Removal: Heavy metals (Cd, Pb, As) via sublimation
· Safety: Off-gas capture and filtration

Stage 6: Biological Priming

· Inoculation: Starter Culture application (1 kg/10 m²)
· Incubation: 14 days at 25°C, 80% humidity
· Activation: Light watering to stimulate microbial growth

6.2 Starter Culture System

Guild Composition:

```
Guild           Species/Strains               Function
-----           ----------------               --------
Nitrogen Fixers Rhizobium spp.                Atmospheric N₂ → NH₃
                Bradyrhizobium japonicum      Legume symbiosis
                Azotobacter vinelandii        Free-living fixation
                
Mineralizers    Bacillus mucilaginosus        K, P, Si solubilization
                Pseudomonas fluorescens       Phosphonate metabolism
                Mycorrhizal fungi (Glomus)    P uptake enhancement
                
Decomposers     Actinobacteria (Streptomyces) Lignin/cellulose breakdown
                Cyanobacteria (Nostoc)        Organic matter accumulation
                Trichoderma spp.              Pathogen suppression
```

Production & Storage:

· Earth preparation: Lyophilized mixed cultures
· Mars multiplication: 100L bioreactors with Martian water
· Storage: Cryogenic (-80°C) with 5-year viability
· Quality control: Monthly viability assays

Application Protocol:

1. Soil temperature: 15–30°C range
2. Moisture: 60–80% field capacity
3. Incorporation: 10 cm depth mixing
4. Activation: Light carbohydrate addition (molasses equivalent)
5. Protection: 7-day no-disturbance period

6.3 Soil Health Monitoring

Parameters & Frequency:

· Daily: Moisture, temperature, pH
· Weekly: Nutrient availability (NPK + micronutrients)
· Monthly: Microbial biomass and diversity (DNA sequencing)
· Quarterly: Soil structure and aggregation
· Annually: Heavy metal residual testing

Remediation Protocols:

· Nutrient depletion: Targeted fertilizer amendment
· pH drift: Buffering agent application
· Microbial decline: Reinoculation from cryostock
· Compaction: Aeration and organic matter addition

