7. EMERGENCY PROTOCOLS FOR DOME BREACH (EPDB)

7.1 Breach Classification System

Level 1: Micro-Perforation

· Size: <1 cm diameter
· Detection: Acoustic sensors + pressure decay (0.001 atm/min)
· Response: Auto-seal patch deployment (aerogel injection)
· Timeline: Containment within 60 seconds

Level 2: Structural Compromise

· Size: 1–30 cm breach
· Detection: Visual confirmation + rapid pressure loss (0.01 atm/min)
· Response: Section isolation + emergency patch team
· Timeline: Containment within 5 minutes

Level 3: Catastrophic Failure

· Size: >30 cm or multiple breaches
· Detection: Explosive decompression (>0.05 atm/sec)
· Response: Full sectionalization + survival tier activation
· Timeline: Complete isolation within 30 seconds

7.2 Automatic Response Sequence

Phase 1: Detection & Alert (0–2 seconds)

· Pressure sensors trigger alarm
· Audio-visual alerts throughout affected zone
· Airlock controls locked to prevent accidental trapping

Phase 2: Isolation & Containment (2–10 seconds)

· Magnetic bulkheads seal (3-second closure)
· Segmented irrigation valves close
· HVAC dampers isolate affected section
· Power reduced to non-essential systems

Phase 3: Stabilization (10–60 seconds)

· Sacrificial CO₂ dump (0.1 atm buffer)
· Thermal blankets deploy over Tier 1/2 zones
· Emergency lighting activates
· Safe-haven sarcophagi unlock

Phase 4: Assessment & Recovery (1 minute–24 hours)

· Robotic assessment of damage
· Human team deployment if safe
· Repair planning and execution
· Gradual re-pressurization if structurally sound

7.3 Survival Tiering Protocol

Tier 1: Genetic & Microbial Preservation

· Contents: Cryogenic seed bank, microbial master cultures
· Protection: 10 cm titanium armor, independent power (30 days)
· Priority: Absolute preservation at all costs
· Location: Central, deepest buried position

Tier 2: Biological Foundation

· Contents: Active Starter Culture bioreactors, pollinator nuclei
· Protection: 5 cm composite armor, 72-hour thermal buffering
· Priority: High preservation (foundation of ecosystem)
· Location: Distributed redundant locations

Tier 3: Caloric Security

· Contents: Mature staple crops (potatoes, grains)
· Protection: Standard dome shielding, CO₂ buffer during breach
· Priority: Moderate preservation (6-month food reserve)
· Location: Main agricultural zones

Tier 4: Nutritional Diversity

· Contents: Fruits, vegetables, herbs
· Protection: Minimal additional protection
· Priority: Replaceable within 3 months
· Location: Peripheral or experimental zones

7.4 Post-Breach Recovery Sequence

Step 1: Structural Integrity Verification

· 3D ultrasonic mapping of entire affected zone
· Stress analysis of remaining structure
· Repair plan generation (human + robotic)

Step 2: Atmospheric Restoration

· Slow re-pressurization (0.01 atm/minute)
· Ethylene and VOC scrubbing (PCO systems)
· Oxygen level normalization (21% partial pressure)

Step 3: Thermal Recovery

· Gradual warming (2°C/hour to avoid thermal shock)
· Soil temperature monitoring (avoiding frozen root damage)
· Microbial activity assessment

Step 4: Biological Assessment & Intervention

· Plant viability survey (multispectral imaging)
· Soil microbe viability testing (ATP assays)
· Reinoculation protocol (2× standard Starter Culture dose)
· Selective replanting based on damage assessment

Step 5: System Normalization

· Gradual reintegration with main systems
· Increased monitoring for 30 days post-event
· Lessons learned integration into AI models

7.5 Emergency Equipment & Infrastructure

Breach Response Kits (Located every 20m):

· Aero-gel patch cartridges (10 cm diameter capacity)
· Emergency oxygen masks (30-minute supply)
· Thermal blankets (multi-layer reflective)
· Manual bulkhead closure override tools
· First aid supplies

Safe-Haven Sarcophagi (One per 100 m²):

· Capacity: 1 person for 2 hours
· Pressure: Independent 0.4 atm supply
· Communication: Radio and hard-line
· Location: Clearly marked with luminescent signage

Robotic First Responders:

· Seal-Bots: Small, agile robots for patch application
· Assess-Bots: Sensor-equipped for damage mapping
· Rescue-Bots: Capable of moving humans to safety

