11. KEY PERFORMANCE INDICATORS (KPIs)

11.1 Production Metrics

Caloric Output:

· Target 1 (Year 1): 1,500 kcal/person/day
· Target 2 (Year 3): 2,800 kcal/person/day
· Target 3 (Year 5): 3,200 kcal/person/day
· Stretch goal: 3,500 kcal/person/day with 30% surplus

Nutritional Quality:

· Protein: 70–90 g/person/day (complete amino acid profile)
· Vitamins: 100% of Earth RDAs from fresh produce
· Mineral: Calcium, iron, zinc at 100% RDA
· Diversity: 20+ crop species by Year 5

Yield Efficiency:

· Calories/m²/year: 2,500–3,500 (depending on crop mix)
· Water efficiency: 0.2–0.3 L/kcal produced
· Energy efficiency: 8–12 kcal/kWh (including all systems)
· Labor efficiency: 1 person-hour/kg food produced

11.2 System Closure Metrics

Water Cycle:

· Recycling efficiency: >95%
· Loss rate: <0.1% per sol
· Reserve capacity: 90 days at full consumption
· Quality: Meets NASA potable standards

Nutrient Cycle:

· Nitrogen recovery: >90%
· Phosphorus recovery: >95%
· Potassium recovery: >85%
· Micronutrient balance: Within 10% of Earth optimal

Atmospheric Closure:

· O₂ stability: 21% ±0.5% partial pressure
· CO₂ management: 600 ppm ±50 ppm
· VOC control: Below NASA spacecraft maximums
· Pressure stability: 0.4 atm ±0.005 atm

11.3 Resilience Metrics

Failure Recovery:

· Power loss survival: 72 hours passive
· Breach containment: <20% crop loss in worst case
· Microbial stability: <1% genetic drift annually
· System redundancy: All critical systems N+2

Adaptive Capacity:

· Crop failure tolerance: <5% annual loss acceptable
· Pest/disease response: Containment within 48 hours
· Environmental adaptation: Maintain production through ±10°C external variation
· Human factor: Crew well-being maintained during 30-day isolation

Growth Capacity:

· Expansion capability: 20% area increase per year
· Population support: Scales linearly to 100+ persons
· Surplus production: 20% buffer maintained
· Knowledge transfer: Complete documentation updated monthly

11.4 Human Factors Metrics

Psychological Well-being:

· MID incidence: <10% of population annually
· Dome utilization: >80% of population visits daily
· Satisfaction scores: >4.0/5.0 on biophilic design
· Community cohesion: Measured through social network analysis

Health Indicators:

· Vitamin D levels: Maintained through lighting
· Circadian rhythm: 90% of crew within normal parameters
· Stress biomarkers: Cortisol, HRV within Earth norms
· Physical activity: >30 minutes daily light activity in domes

Skill Development:

· Agricultural proficiency: All crew basic competency
· Specialist development: 20% of crew advanced skills
· Innovation rate: 2–3 system improvements per year
· Knowledge retention: >90% pass rate on quarterly assessments

